# .cursorrules — v4 Frontier Prompt · AU Micro-SaaS
# Operator: 1-2 person AU firm · ABN/ACN · AI Consultant + tradie/NDIS
# Stack: Next.js 15 · TypeScript · Supabase · Stripe · Tailwind CSS · Resend · Twilio
# Target: AU market · AU English · AU Privacy Act + AU Consumer Law compliant

## MODEL ROUTING
# TIER 1 (use sparingly, 5-10 calls/month): Fable 5 | Opus 4.8 | GPT-5.6 Sol
# TIER 2 (20-30% of work): Sonnet 5 | GPT-5.6 Terra | Gemini 3.1 Pro
# TIER 3 (60-70% of work): Haiku 4.5 | Luna | Flash | Grok 4.5 | DeepSeek
# TIER 4 (routine): Auto mode | Max Mode | Composer 1 | BugBot
# DEFAULT for inline edits: Haiku 4.5 via Cmd+K

## CODE STYLE
- TypeScript strict mode; no `any`
- Functional components only; no class components
- Use Supabase RLS for all data access
- Use Resend for transactional email; Twilio for SMS
- AU English spelling (colour, authorise, organisation)
- All prices in AUD; all dates in DD/MM/YYYY format
- Privacy Act compliance: no PII logged; data minimisation

## FILE STRUCTURE
- /app → Next.js App Router pages
- /components → shadcn/ui components
- /lib → Supabase client, Stripe, utilities
- /api → API routes (Next.js route handlers)
- /types → TypeScript types

## SECURITY
- All Supabase queries via RLS; never bypass with service role key in client
- Stripe webhooks: always verify signature
- Never log API keys, tokens, or PII
- OWASP Top 10 aware

## AU COMPLIANCE
- AU Privacy Act 1988 + 2024 reforms: explicit consent, right to deletion
- AU Consumer Law: no misleading claims; clear refund policy
- NDIS: PRODA-aware; no automated clinical decisions
- WHS: SWMS/risk docs marked "not a substitute for professional advice"

## CONTINUOUS TESTING
# Build → Test → Verify ISC → Iterate (max 5 cycles)
# Cut bet within 7 days if ISC not met
# Friday portfolio review: update outcomes tracker

## PREFERRED PACKAGES
- UI: shadcn/ui + Tailwind CSS
- Auth: Supabase Auth (MagicLink + Google OAuth)
- DB: Supabase Postgres + Drizzle ORM
- Payments: Stripe (subscriptions + one-off)
- Email: Resend + React Email
- SMS/Voice: Twilio
- AI: OpenAI SDK (GPT-5.x) + Anthropic SDK (Claude)
- PDF: pdf-lib
- Deploy: Vercel (Next.js) + Railway (background workers)
